---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import AdUnit from "../../components/AdUnit.astro";
---
<Base title="Preply Review 2026: Is It Worth Your Money?" description="Our in-depth Preply review covers pricing, tutor quality, and key features. Find out if Preply is right for you.">
  <Header />
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <div class="mb-6">
      <span class="text-sm text-neutral-400">Review · Updated April 2026</span>
    </div>

    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4 leading-tight">
      Preply Review 2026: Is It Worth Your Money?
    </h1>

    <p class="text-xl text-neutral-300 mb-8 leading-relaxed">
      Preply connects you with over 100,000 tutors worldwide for 1-on-1 video lessons. We tested it for three months and here is our honest verdict.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-[#1a1f2e] border border-neutral-700 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-10">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between gap-4">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-1">Our Rating</p>
          <p class="text-5xl font-bold text-white">8.5<span class="text-xl text-neutral-400">/10</span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-left sm:text-right">
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-1">Best For</p>
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">Flexible, personalized lessons</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-amber-900/20 border border-amber-700/30 rounded-xl p-4 mb-8">
      <p class="text-sm text-amber-200/80">
        <strong>Affiliate disclosure:</strong> We earn a commission when you sign up through links on this page, at no extra cost to you. Our reviews are based on real research and are never influenced by compensation.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-[#1e2a1a] border border-green-700/30 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-green-400 mb-2">Quick Verdict</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
        Preply is an excellent choice if you want full control over your learning schedule and the ability to choose from thousands of tutors across every time zone. The platform is easy to use, prices are transparent, and tutors are generally well-vetted. The main downside is quality can vary significantly between tutors. We rate it 8.5/10 and recommend starting with a trial lesson before committing.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-[#1a1f2e] border border-neutral-700 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-4">In This Review</h2>
      <ol class="space-y-2 text-neutral-300">
        <li><a href="#what-is-preply" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">What Is Preply?</a></li>
        <li><a href="#how-does-preply-work" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">How Does Preply Work?</a></li>
        <li><a href="#pricing" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Preply Pricing</a></li>
        <li><a href="#teacher-quality" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Teacher Quality</a></li>
        <li><a href="#key-features" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Key Features</a></li>
        <li><a href="#pros" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Pros</a></li>
        <li><a href="#cons" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Cons</a></li>
        <li><a href="#verdict" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Verdict</a></li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <h2 id="what-is-preply" class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">What Is Preply?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Preply is an online language tutoring marketplace that connects learners with tutors from around the world for live, 1-on-1 video lessons. Founded in 2012 and headquartered in Austin, Texas, the platform has grown to feature more than 100,000 tutors teaching over 50 languages.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Unlike platforms where you are assigned a tutor, Preply lets you browse profiles, read reviews, watch intro videos, and book lessons with whoever fits your learning style. You can take lessons anytime, day or night, because tutors span every time zone.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      Preply is particularly popular among English learners because it offers tutors from native English-speaking countries as well as non-native tutors who speak your language. This makes it easier to find a tutor who understands your specific challenges.
    </p>

    <h2 id="how-does-preply-work" class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">How Does Preply Work?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Getting started with Preply is straightforward. You create a free account, set your language level, and start browsing tutors. Each tutor profile shows their hourly rate, availability, specializations, student reviews, and a short intro video.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Once you find a tutor you like, you can book a trial lesson at a discounted rate (usually around $5-$20 depending on the tutor). This gives you a chance to see if their teaching style works for you before committing to regular lessons.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      Lessons take place on Preply own own video platform, which includes a virtual whiteboard, screen sharing, and the ability to upload materials. You can also reschedule lessons up to 24 hours before the session, which gives you flexibility if your schedule changes.
    </p>

    <h2 id="pricing" class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Preply Pricing</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Preply does not use a subscription model. Instead, you pay per lesson, and prices vary significantly depending on the tutor you choose. Here is a general breakdown of what to expect:
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-[#1e2a3a]">
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-white font-semibold">Tutor Tier</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-white font-semibold">Hourly Rate</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-white font-semibold">Best For</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-neutral-700">
          <tr class="bg-[#1a1f2e]">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-300">Community Tutors</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-300">$5 - $15/hr</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-300">Conversation practice, budget learners</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-[#1e2a3a]">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-300">Certified Tutors</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-300">$15 - $40/hr</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-300">Structured lessons, exam prep</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-[#1a1f2e]">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-300">Expert Tutors</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-300">$40 - $100+/hr</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-neutral-300">Business English, advanced learners</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Most learners on Preply work with certified tutors in the $15-$30/hour range. You can also buy lesson packages of 10 or 20 sessions for a small discount, which can bring the effective hourly rate down by 5-15%.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      One thing to note: if you cancel your subscription or stop lessons, any unused credits stay in your account. There is no monthly minimum commitment, which makes Preply more flexible than subscription-based platforms like Cambly.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-blue-900/20 border border-blue-600/30 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-10">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Looking for a More Affordable Option?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        See Guru offers structured lessons with certified tutors starting at $5/hr. It is a solid alternative if you want lower prices without sacrificing quality.
      </p>
      <a href="/go/see-guru/" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored nofollow" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-xl transition-colors">
        Compare See Guru vs Preply
      </a>
    </div>

    <h2 id="teacher-quality" class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Teacher Quality</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Teacher quality on Preply varies more than on platforms like Cambly or iTalki, where tutors go through a more formal vetting process. Preply allows tutors to set up profiles directly, which means anyone can theoretically offer lessons.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      That said, Preply does have quality signals built into the platform. Tutors with higher ratings and more completed lessons appear higher in search results. Look for tutors with at least 50 completed lessons and a 4.8-star rating or higher before making your decision.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      Certified tutors on Preply have completed Preply internal training program and passed a teaching certification. These tutors typically charge more but tend to deliver more structured lessons with clear learning plans.
    </p>

    <h2 id="key-features" class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Key Features</h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Preply Tutor Marketplace</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Preply gives you access to over 100,000 tutors. You can filter by native language, accent preference, specializations (business English, IELTS prep, conversation practice), and availability. This variety means you are more likely to find a tutor who matches your specific needs.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Trial Lessons</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Most tutors on Preply offer a trial lesson at a reduced rate. This is a great way to test whether a tutor is the right fit before committing to a full lesson package. We recommend trying at least two or three tutors before settling on one.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Preply Spaces</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Preply Spaces is a virtual classroom feature that lets you practice writing, use interactive exercises, and review lesson recordings. It is available on the web and mobile app, so you can continue learning even between live sessions.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-3">Corporate Training</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      For businesses, Preply offers team plans with dedicated account managers, progress tracking, and group sessions. This makes it a viable option for companies looking to upskill their employees in English.
    </p>

    <h2 id="pros" class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Pros</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">Huge tutor selection:</strong> Over 100,000 tutors means you will find someone who fits your schedule, budget, and learning goals.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">No subscription required:</strong> Pay per lesson with no monthly commitment. Stop anytime without losing money.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">Trial lessons available:</strong> Test a tutor before committing with reduced-rate trial sessions.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">Global time zone coverage:</strong> Tutors available 24 hours a day, seven days a week.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">Preply Spaces:</strong> A useful supplemental learning tool with exercises and lesson recordings.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-green-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10003;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">Flexible rescheduling:</strong> Reschedule lessons up to 24 hours before the session at no charge.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="cons" class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Cons</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-red-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10007;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">Inconsistent tutor quality:</strong> Because anyone can set up a profile, some tutors lack formal teaching qualifications.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-red-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10007;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">No fixed curriculum:</strong> You or your tutor sets the lesson agenda. This requires more self-direction than structured platforms.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-red-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10007;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">Video platform limitations:</strong> The built-in video tool works well enough, but it lacks some features found in dedicated video conferencing tools.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-red-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10007;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">Currency conversion fees:</strong> Depending on your payment method, you may face additional fees.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-neutral-300">
        <span class="text-red-400 mt-1 text-lg flex-shrink-0">&#10007;</span>
        <span><strong class="text-white">Cancellations:</strong> Some tutors cancel lessons at short notice, especially those who are part-time on the platform.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="verdict" class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4">Verdict</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      Preply earns an 8.5 out of 10 on our scale. It is one of the most flexible tutoring platforms available, giving learners full control over who they study with, when, and at what price. The sheer variety of tutors is its biggest strength.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-4 leading-relaxed">
      The platform works best for motivated learners who know what they want to achieve. If you want structured lessons with a clear curriculum, look for a Preply tutor who specializes in your target area. Check our <a href="/reviews/italki/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">iTalki review</a> or <a href="/reviews/cambly/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Cambly review</a> for comparison.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-300 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
      The main risk with Preply is ending up with a tutor who is not a good fit. That is why we strongly recommend using trial lessons to shop around. Most good tutors fill up quickly, so book your favorites early.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-[#1a1f2e] border border-neutral-700 rounded-2xl p-6 mb-10">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between flex-wrap gap-4">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-1">Overall Rating</p>
          <p class="text-4xl font-bold text-white">8.5<span class="text-xl text-neutral-400">/10</span></p>
        </div>
        <div class="text-right">
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-400 mb-1">Get Started From</p>
          <p class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">$5 per lesson</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-4 mb-10">
      <details class="bg-[#1a1f2e] border border-neutral-700 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-white font-semibold cursor-pointer hover:bg-neutral-800/50">Is Preply good for beginners?</summary>
        <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          Yes. Preply is suitable for beginners, but look for tutors who specialize in teaching beginners or hold a teaching certification. Community tutors at the lower price range may not have the skills to help a complete beginner effectively.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="bg-[#1a1f2e] border border-neutral-700 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-white font-semibold cursor-pointer hover:bg-neutral-800/50">How much does Preply cost per month?</summary>
        <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          Preply does not require a monthly subscription. You pay per lesson, with prices ranging from $5 to over $100 per hour depending on the tutor. If you take two lessons per week at $20 per session, you can expect to spend around $160 per month.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="bg-[#1a1f2e] border border-neutral-700 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-white font-semibold cursor-pointer hover:bg-neutral-800/50">Can I change tutors on Preply?</summary>
        <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          Yes. You can book lessons with as many different tutors as you want. Many learners work with two or three tutors simultaneously, using one for conversation practice and another for structured grammar lessons.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="bg-[#1a1f2e] border border-neutral-700 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-white font-semibold cursor-pointer hover:bg-neutral-800/50">Does Preply offer a free trial?</summary>
        <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          Preply does not offer a platform-wide free trial. However, individual tutors set their own trial lesson prices, and many offer trial lessons for $5 to $20. This gives you a low-cost way to test the platform.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="bg-[#1a1f2e] border border-neutral-700 rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="px-5 py-4 text-white font-semibold cursor-pointer hover:bg-neutral-800/50">How is Preply different from iTalki?</summary>
        <p class="px-5 pb-4 text-neutral-300 leading-relaxed">
          Both platforms connect you with tutors for 1-on-1 lessons. The main difference is that Preply offers a wider range of tutor prices and does not require a monthly subscription, while iTalki has a more structured community tutor option. For a full comparison, see our <a href="/compare/preply-vs-italki/" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Preply vs iTalki guide</a>.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>

    <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is Preply good for beginners?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. Preply is suitable for beginners, but look for tutors who specialize in teaching beginners or hold a teaching certification."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much does Preply cost per month?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Preply does not require a monthly subscription. You pay per lesson, with prices ranging from $5 to over $100 per hour depending on the tutor."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can I change tutors on Preply?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Yes. You can book lessons with as many different tutors as you want on Preply."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Does Preply offer a free trial?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Preply does not offer a platform-wide free trial, but individual tutors offer trial lessons for $5 to $20."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How is Preply different from iTalki?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Both connect you with tutors for 1-on-1 lessons. Preply offers a wider range of tutor prices and no monthly subscription, while iTalki has a more structured community tutor option."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
    </script>
  
    <aside class="mt-12 mb-4 p-6 bg-slate-900/60 border border-slate-700 rounded-xl">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Compare with other platforms</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-base">
        <li><a href="/reviews/see-guru/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300"><strong>See Guru</strong> <span class="text-slate-400 font-normal">3 free 1-on-1 lessons with real teachers</span></a></li>
        <li><a href="/reviews/italki/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300"><strong>iTalki</strong> <span class="text-slate-400 font-normal">Largest tutor marketplace, 10M+ learners</span></a></li>
        <li><a href="/reviews/cambly/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300"><strong>Cambly</strong> <span class="text-slate-400 font-normal">Unlimited talk time with native speakers</span></a></li>
        <li><a href="/reviews/lingoda/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300"><strong>Lingoda</strong> <span class="text-slate-400 font-normal">Class-based marathon programs with certificates</span></a></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-5 pt-5 border-t border-slate-700 text-sm text-slate-300">
        New here? Start with our <a href="/blog/how-long-to-learn-english/" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 underline">CEFR reality check</a> to see how many hours your target really takes.
      </p>
    </aside>

  </article>
  <Footer />
</Base>
